<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 14:37:09 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>氢测试了量子虫洞猜想</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/hydrogen-puts-quantum-wormhole-conjecture-to-the-test</link><description>一个新的&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hydrogen-puts-quantum-wormhole-conjecture-to-the-test2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 14:37:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/hydrogen-puts-quantum-wormhole-conjecture-to-the-test</guid></item><item><title>“蝴蝶”分子终于被发现，完成了长达20年的量子动物园狩猎</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/butterfly-molecule-spotted-at-last-completing-a-20-year-quantum-zoo-hunt</link><description>二十年来，物理学家一直预测存在一个非凡的奇异分子家族：巨大的原子与普通原子结合，电子距离原子核如此之远，以至于将这对分子塑造成奇异而多样的形状。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/butterfly-molecule-spotted-at-last-completing-a-20-year-quantum-zoo-hunt2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 14:22:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/butterfly-molecule-spotted-at-last-completing-a-20-year-quantum-zoo-hunt</guid></item><item><title>韦伯透露，宇宙中最遥远的“热狗”可能因极地尘埃而发出极端的红外光</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/universes-most-distant-hot-dog-yet-may-owe-extreme-infrared-glow-to-polar-dust-webb-reveals</link><description>詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜的新观测揭示了宇宙中最明亮的已知天体之一的新细节：尘埃覆盖的类星体 W2246−0526，在大爆炸后仅 12 亿年就被观测到。概述结果的论文发表在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/universes-most-distant-hot-dog-yet-may-owe-extreme-infrared-glow-to-polar-dust-webb-reveals.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 14:07:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/universes-most-distant-hot-dog-yet-may-owe-extreme-infrared-glow-to-polar-dust-webb-reveals</guid></item><item><title>当你宽恕时，你的大脑不会忘记——它会对那些痛苦的记忆做出更令人惊讶的事情</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/your-brain-doesnt-forget-when-you-forgive-it-does-something-far-more-surprising-with-those-painful-memories</link><description>原谅某人可能不会消除痛苦的记忆，但它可以巧妙地更新它们，让过去的伤害不再那么令人沮丧。它不再是“原谅和忘记”，而是更多的“原谅和更新”。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/your-brain-doesnt-forget-when-you-forgive-it-does-something-far-more-surprising-with-those-painful-memories.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 13:52:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/your-brain-doesnt-forget-when-you-forgive-it-does-something-far-more-surprising-with-those-painful-memories</guid></item><item><title>新的镁合金设计提高了固态电池的稳定性和离子传输</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-magnesium-alloy-design-improves-stability-and-ion-transport-in-solid-state-batteries</link><description>现代世界依靠无形的能量运转。隐藏在智能手机、笔记本电脑和电动汽车内部的电池为日常生活悄悄供电。随着社会越来越依赖便携式和可持续能源，开发紧凑且可靠的电池技术已成为当今时代最重要的技术挑战之一。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-magnesium-alloy-design-improves-stability-and-ion-transport-in-solid-state-batteries2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 13:37:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-magnesium-alloy-design-improves-stability-and-ion-transport-in-solid-state-batteries</guid></item><item><title>用激光发现新的三维磁结构</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-three-dimensional-magnetic-structure-discovered-with-laser-light</link><description>飞秒激光的闪光只持续几万亿分之一秒，使得人们首次观察到新的磁结构。通过使用光作为遥控器，研究人员能够将磁性切换到纳米尺度上以前未见过的三维状态。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-three-dimensional-magnetic-structure-discovered-with-laser-light.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 13:22:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-three-dimensional-magnetic-structure-discovered-with-laser-light</guid></item><item><title>太阳能电池增压：量子点-分子混合态可实现接近最大的效率</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/supercharging-solar-cells-quantum-dot-molecule-hybrid-states-enable-near-maximum-efficiency</link><description>多年来，太阳能电池板的效率已经变得越来越高，但即使是最好的设计仍然会损失其吸收的大部分能量。世界各地的科学家一直在寻找从每一缕阳光中捕获更多能量并释放太阳能技术真正潜力的方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/supercharging-solar-cells-quantum-dot-molecule-hybrid-states-enable-near-maximum-efficiency3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 13:07:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/supercharging-solar-cells-quantum-dot-molecule-hybrid-states-enable-near-maximum-efficiency</guid></item><item><title>随机化可以提高量子计算机在存在噪声的情况下的性能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/randomization-can-improve-quantum-computer-performance-in-presence-of-noise</link><description>由即将毕业的博士领导的新研究新墨西哥大学电气与计算机工程系的学生表明，随机化可以提高量子计算机在存在噪声的情况下的性能。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/randomization-can-improve-quantum-computer-performance-in-presence-of-noise2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 12:52:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/randomization-can-improve-quantum-computer-performance-in-presence-of-noise</guid></item><item><title>可视化扑动踢垂直涡流如何产生推进力并抑制游泳者的身体摇摆</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/visualizing-how-flutter-kick-vertical-vortices-generate-propulsion-and-suppress-body-sway-in-swimmers</link><description>筑波大学的研究人员使用先进技术对前泳时扑腿产生的水流进行可视化。他们分析了这种踢腿运动如何产生推进力并有助于身体稳定，证明左右腿交替运动产生的垂直涡流不仅可以提供向前的推进力，还可以抑制身体的摇摆。这些结果为颤振踢的功能价值提供了流体动力学解释。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/visualizing-how-flutter-kick-vertical-vortices-generate-propulsion-and-suppress-body-sway-in-swimmers2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 12:37:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/visualizing-how-flutter-kick-vertical-vortices-generate-propulsion-and-suppress-body-sway-in-swimmers</guid></item><item><title>人工智能加速下一代计算机芯片和电子材料的发现</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-speeds-up-discovery-of-next-gen-computer-chips-and-electronic-materials</link><description>由弗林德斯大学领导的一个国际研究团队与阿联酋哈利法大学合作，建立了一个机器学习平台，就像一个“智能材料发现引擎”，它能够大大减少复杂的计算机或实验室实验所花费的时间，以测试和寻找未来半导体的新材料。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-speeds-up-discovery-of-next-gen-computer-chips-and-electronic-materials.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 12:22:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-speeds-up-discovery-of-next-gen-computer-chips-and-electronic-materials</guid></item></channel></rss>